# kindleweather

Simple Kindle-friendly weather display for Cloudflare Pages.

It shows the latest temperature (`tl`), relative humidity (`rf`), and timestamp
from the Pottschach TAWES endpoint. The browser calls `/api/weather`; the
Cloudflare Pages Function fetches the upstream data server-side to avoid CORS
issues.

## Cloudflare Pages

No build step is required.

- Build command: leave empty
- Build output directory: `/`
- Functions directory: `functions`

The page refreshes its data every ten minutes. A HTML meta refresh is also
included as a fallback for older Kindle browsers.
